dcterms:description: Synthetic data were generated by obtaining the dynamics of Koopman embeddings in a two-dimensional Koopman space with a randomly generated linear transition matrix, followed by a nonlinear transformation using a randomly generated three-layered feed-forward neural network.
dcterms:title: Synthetic

dcterms:creator: B. Van der Pol
dcterms:description: The Van-der-Pol data were generated using the van der Pol oscillator, a non-conservative oscillator with nonlinear damping, used in various scientific fields.
dcterms:title: Van-der-Pol

dcterms:creator: E. N. Lorenz
dcterms:description: The Lorenz data were generated using the Lorenz system, which has chaotic solutions and is developed for atmospheric convection.
dcterms:title: Lorenz

dcterms:description: The Cylinder-wake data were generated using a fluid dynamics simulator, sampling time-series with different dynamics based on grid locations and Reynolds numbers.
dcterms:title: Cylinder-wake
